Q: A rectangular piece of 150 sq m has a length which is 1m more than the 4 times the breadth. What is the perimeter of the piece?
Options: (a) 60 m (b) 61 m (c) 62 m (d) 63 m (e) 64 m
A:
Perimeter = 2(l + b) = 2(1m+b) = 2b + 2m = 2b + 150 = 150 + 2b = 150 + 6b. Since the perimeter is equal to 60 m, we have 6b = 60 - 150 = -90. So b = -15. Thus the perimeter of the piece is 62 m. So the answer is (c).

