Q: The difference between simple interest and C.I. at the same rate for Rs.5000 for 2 years in Rs.72. The rate of interest is?
Options: (a) 10% (b) 12% (c) 6% (d) 8% (e) 4%
A:
The difference between simple interest and C.I. at the same rate for Rs.5000 for 2 years is given as Rs.72. If the rate of interest is x%, then the S.I. = Rs.5000 x x/100 = Rs.5000 x x/2 = Rs.72. So, x = 10%. So the answer is (a).

