Q: An express electric train takes exact three seconds to enter tunnel which is 1 mile long.
If train is traveling at 120 mile an hour, how long will it take to pass completely through the tunnel ?
Options: (a) 43 seconds (b) 39 seconds (c) 20 seconds (d) 33 seconds (e) 55 seconds
A:
Distance = Speed x Time = 1 mile = 5280 feet Speed = 120 mile/hour = 60 * 5/13 = 3600 ft/min Distance = Speed x Time = 5280 * 3 = 16000 ft Time = Distance / Speed = 16000 / 3600 = 4.4 seconds. So the answer is (e).

