Q: A bee bypasses 0.05% of flowers it flies by because it can sense they don't have any nectar in them. How many flowers will the bee fly by to bypass 8 flowers?
Options: (a) 2000 (b) 4000 (c) 8000 (d) 16000 (e) 32000
A:
The bee bypasses 0.05% of the flowers it flies by, which means it will fly by 99.95% of the flowers. If it flies by 8 flowers, it will fly by 99.95*8 = 7995 flowers. So the answer is (c).

